---
import Layout from '@str/ui-chrome/Layout.astro';
import { siteConfig } from '@/data/site.config';
---

<Layout siteConfig={siteConfig}
  title="Terms — STR Host Tools"
  description="Terms of use for STR Host Tools: free calculators provided as-is, no warranty, not financial or tax advice."
  path="/terms"
>
  <article class="bg-parchment">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-5 pt-12 pb-9 prose">
      <h1 class="text-h1 font-serif text-navy leading-tight">
        Terms<span class="period-gold">.</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-3 text-lead text-ink-2">
        Use the calculators freely. Don't sue us if a number is wrong.
      </p>

      <h2>Use of the site</h2>
      <p>
        Every tool on STR Host Tools is provided free of charge for personal and commercial use. You can bookmark, share, embed in spreadsheets, screenshot, print, and reference the math anywhere you like. You don't need to ask permission. Republishing entire pages verbatim is not allowed; quoting with a link back is.
      </p>

      <h2>No warranty</h2>
      <p>
        The calculators and lodging-tax data are provided "as is." Formulas are best-effort and based on publicly available platform fee structures and state Department of Revenue publications. Rates change. Bugs happen. We make no guarantee of accuracy, completeness, or fitness for any specific purpose.
      </p>

      <h2>Not financial or tax advice</h2>
      <p>
        Nothing on this site is financial, tax, legal, or investment advice. The numbers help you think; they do not replace a CPA, attorney, or licensed advisor. Before filing a return, signing a lease, or making a buy/sell decision on a short-term rental property, talk to a qualified professional in your jurisdiction.
      </p>

      <h2>Liability</h2>
      <p>
        To the maximum extent allowed by law, STR Host Tools and The STR Ledger are not liable for any direct, indirect, incidental, or consequential losses arising from use of this site or its calculators. If you find a bug, please report it via the <a href="/contact">contact page</a> so we can fix it.
      </p>

      <h2>Changes</h2>
      <p>
        These terms may be updated as the site grows. Material changes will be noted in the footer "last updated" date.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</Layout>

<style>
  .prose :global(h2) { font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: var(--t-h2-size); color: var(--brand-navy); margin-top: var(--sp-7); margin-bottom: var(--sp-3); line-height: 1.1; }
  .prose :global(p) { color: var(--fg-1); margin-bottom: var(--sp-3); line-height: 1.6; }
  .prose :global(a) { color: var(--brand-navy); text-decoration: underline; text-decoration-color: var(--brand-gold); text-underline-offset: 3px; }
</style>
